Package: MONET
Type: Package
Title: Model of Neutral Evolution of Traits
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Isabela", "do O", email = "isabela.doo@unil.ch", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Oscar E", "Gaggiotti", role = "aut"),
    person("Pierre", "de Villemereuil", role = "aut"),
    person("Jerome", "Goudet", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Implements a Bayesian linear mixed-effects model of neutral trait
    evolution in spatially structured populations. It then allows for a series of
    hypothesis testing such as for local or global adaptation
    by comparing two estimates of ancestral additive genetic variance derived from
    between-population divergence and within-population variation, using coancestry
    matrices to explicitly model population structure. It also allows for other tests
    such as testing for correlation between trait divergence and environmental patterns.
